{"type":"message","id":"c306f22d","parentId":"961d1d44","timestamp":"2026-04-06T09:43:06.559Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `scada-object-explore` skill is used to explore live SCADA objects, allowing you to find and retrieve information about substations, telemetry points, and other system elements. Here are the basic steps to use it:\n\n1. **Identify the pattern**: Determine the pattern that matches the objects you want to search for. For substations, this would typically be `/substation`.\n\n2. **Run the skill**: Use the `skill_run` tool with the identified pattern.\n\n### Example\n\nTo list all substations in your SCADA project:\n\n1. Identify the pattern: `/substation`\n2. Run the skill:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"skill_run\",\n  \"arguments\": {\n    \"skill\": \"scada-object-explore\",\n    \"params\": {\n      \"pattern\": \"/substation\"\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nThis will return a list of substations and their associated details.\n\nFeel free to adjust the pattern or add additional parameters as needed for more specific queries."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-192-168-20-122-11434","model":"qwen2.5-coder:14b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775468581155,"responseId":"chatcmpl-827"}}
